article.headline: Wright St. 77, Marshall 70
article.story: FAIRBORN, Ohio (AP) -- Todd Brown scored 23 points and Vaughn Duggins added 21 to lead Wright State to a 77-70 win over Marshall on Wednesday night. Wright State (2-0) led by as many as 12 points when Duggins made a pair for free throws with 10:34 left to make it 52-40. Marshall (3-1) fought back, getting a 3-pointer from Taurean Marshall with 17 seconds remaining that cut the lead to 75-70. But Duggins again made two free throws for the Raiders to keep the game out of reach. Mark Dorris led Marshall with 20 points. Markel Humphrey scored 12 and Taurean Marshall finished with 15. The Raiders shot 42.2 (19 of 45) percent for the game, and Marshall shot 42.3 percent (22 of 52).
